# core.autocrlf=true on this repo's Windows checkouts converts LF to CRLF on
# checkout by default - fine for most text files, but fatal for a script
# with a #!/bin/sh shebang line: a CRLF line ending makes the interpreter
# path "/bin/sh\r", which the kernel can't find, and the container's build
# silently breaks. Force LF regardless of platform/autocrlf settings for
# anything that runs inside a Linux container.
*.sh text eol=lf
